description: Think you know all you can possibly know about Naruto? Think again! The Official Fanbook takes you deeper than ever before into the world of the most determined ninja as he pushes ever closer to his ultimate destiny! Maps, character profiles, previously hidden revelations and more give you all the inside secrets about Masashi Kishimoto's incredible saga. Includes the original 44-page Naruto manga!
name: SC

description:
Naruto and Squad Seven are assigned to an A-ranked mission to protect popular actress, Yukie Fujikaze. They head towards the filming location in Yukinokuni (land of snow), where three snow ninjas wearing the karakuri-shikake-no-yori await! Why are they after Yukie? And will Naruto and his team be able to protect her and escape?!

Yukinokuni is controlled by the Kazebana Doto, who took power after leading a rebellion. Yukie, who survived the upheaval, is the true heir to the land. She is the Koyukihime Princess. She is captured and taken aaway by Doto, along with the six-sided crystal, the key to the treasures – but not without Naruto in pursuit. Now in enemy territory, his Chakra is suppressed leaving him in a desperate situation!
name: Ninja Clash in the Land of Snow

description: Naruto, Shikamaru and Sakura are returning a lost ferret to its owner: the easiest mission ever. Or so they think! When a young knight, Temujin, attacks them out of nowhere, they are drawn into a fierce struggle over a treasure harboring legendary power--the Stone of Gelel. Temujin's master wants to use the stone to create a utopia, while the last of the clan that controlled the stone wants to keep it sealed away forever. When the dream of utopia becomes a nightmare, it'll take a ninja to set things right!
name: Legend of the Stone of Gelel

description: The latest mission for Naruto, Sakura and Rock Lee sure sounds easy: escorting Prince Michiru and his son Hikaru home to the beautiful Crescent Moon Kingdom. But the royal family turns out to be a royal pain, especially after Michiru buys his son an entire circus as a souvenir! Naruto and his teammates find themselves training wild animals while the spoiled princes treat them more like servants than shinobi. But when Michiru and Hikaru return home to a villainous uprising, they discover there are some problems money can't solve. Can Hikaru learn what's really important--and find the strength of a true ruler--in time to help his new ninja friends save the kingdom?
name: Guardians of the Crescent Moon Kingdom

description: Powerful, supple, and sensual - these are words best used to describe the art of TC Cor, an illustrator with an expert eye for the way flesh glistens and muscles ripple on the female form. His newest 'bodies' of work have been assembled in this meticulous collection and is a magnificent gallery of pencil and airbrush illustrations.
name: SC

volume.name: Body Shots: Art of TC Cor

name: Anime Comics Ge

volume.name: Gekijōban Naruto: Daikatsugeki! Yukihime Ninpocho Dattebayo!!

description: It's time to infect the masses this C-Day! This special book is a stark introduction to the horrific world of the Crossed featuring the original #0 issue by Ennis and Burrows as well as teasers for all the trades and the new Badlands series! Available during Crossed C-Day events at your local comic book retailers you can see for yourself why there is no help. There is no hope. There is no escape. There are only the Crossed. Ask your store how to get a copy and celebrate C-Day with the rest of us psychopaths!
Proper Japanese Name: アニメコミック (上)
name: Anime Comics Jō

volume.name: Gekijōban Naruto: Daikatsugeki! Yukihime Ninpocho Dattebayo!!

description: Barbara Jensen is one of those delightful treats in the male-artist dominated world of pin-up artwork. She combines what a man wants to see with how a woman wants to seen! The resulting images are sensual, sexy, and downright adorable! Jensen explores expression, emotion, and plenty of exquisite flesh!
name: Clothing Optional!

volume.name: Double Assassinat Dans La Rue Morgue

name: Il faut sauver la pythie Salpetria

description:
Thrashing Trash Into Trees!

In a world of powerful celestial beings, an epic contest is being conducted to select the next king! Each Celestial selects a kid in junior high to be his champion and grants him a special power. The kids battle it out--losers are eliminated, and the winners are granted new talents!

Seemingly ordinary Kosuke Ueki has been chosen to be a contender in the tournament. Granted the power to change trash into trees, Ueki has two disadvantages to overcome--one, he doesn't know he's a participant in the tournament, and two, how the heck can anyone win a battle with the power to turn trash into trees?
name: Vol. 1

description:
Thrashing Trash Into Trees!

Ueki begins to face off against opponents in the deadly tournament, but will his environmentally friendly ability hold up against more lethal powers like changing water into flames and changing towels into iron? Then Ueki discovers that there's a reward for winning the whole tournament--you get any power of your choice! But the penalties in this game could be more than he bargained for...
name: Vol. 2

description:
Thrashing Trash Into Trees!

Ueki encounters nasty Robert Haydn, a contestant whose very name strikes fear into the hearts of the most seasoned champions. Ueki has been warned to avoid this nutcase at any cost, but his sense of justice won't let him stay away. Will the power of trees stand up to the preeminent favorite of the tournament?
name: Vol. 3

description:
Farewell, Mr. K?

When Ueki's celestial sponsor Mr. K breaks the rules of the game and interferes in a battle, he is banished to the underworld. But Mr. K's selfless act inspires Ueki to go for the win. In order to be the final victor, Ueki must defeat a deadly team of contestants called Roberts 10--led by callous and cruel Robert Haydn. Will turning trash into trees carry the day?
name: Vol. 4

description:
If You Can't Beat 'Em...

Robert's 10, a powerful block of contestants led by notoriously cruel and vicious Robert Haydn, seems to be invincible. Unbelievably, Ueki accepts Robert's invitation to join the team! Could this mean that Ueki has forsaken his morals and sense of justice just to be with the winners?!
name: Vol. 5

description:
Celestial Power!

Could it be true? The tournament takes a surprising turn when Ueki finds out that he and his archrival Robert Haydn are both Celestials. With this knowledge comes new rules, new powers and a whole different outlook on the game. It's not just about trash anymore!
name: Vol. 6

description:
Celestial Power!

Kosuke Ueki has vowed to take on the powerful Robert's 10 group! Ueki's has already eliminated seven of them, but now he's up against Taro Myojin, a contestant that has been granted two lethal powers--the power to turn whistles into laser beams and the power to turn cards into saws. Hey, isn't that against the rules?
name: Vol. 7

description:
Celestial Power!

Welcome to Dogura Mansion--amusement park of the underworld! Ueki and his allies have entered a deadly game against five members of Robert's 10 in a mini-battle tournament! Set in five funky fields, two bouts have already been fought, with one win for Ueki's team and one draw. And for some reason, Ueki's old pal Seiichiro Sano is fighting for the other side in this one. What's a tree-loving do-gooder like Ueki to do?
name: Vol. 8

description:
Celestial Power!

The new, celestially powered-up Ueki finally faces Robert in battle! But this encounter only succeeds in making Ueki realize that Robert is more powerful than he ever could have imagined. Outmatched, overpowered and with the odds astronomically against his favor, Ueki is in an impossible situation. Of course, this never stopped him before...

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 77: Laughter Echoing In the Darkness
  • Chapter 78: Ueki's Justice
  • Chapter 79: The Gap Between Them
  • Chapter 80: Damage
  • Chapter 81: Sano and Rinko
  • Chapter 82: The Reason To Keep On Fighting
  • Chapter 83: Right On!!
  • Chapter 84: No Choice
  • Chapter 85: Hanon
  • Chapter 86: Encounter
name: Vol. 9

description:
All Quiet on the Ueki Front...

Who knew these battles were just the first round? How many rounds are there, anyway?! With only three weeks to put together a five-person team for the second round, Ueki and best pal Ai are hard-pressed to choose fighters who not only compliment their strengths, but can be trusted. Fortunately, they've got a relaxing, uneventful period in which to consider their options, during which no completely unexpected incredibly significant development occurs...right? Right?!
name: Vol. 10

description:
All Quiet on the Ueki Front...

The King's messenger comes to our team supreme--Mori, Sano, Hideyoshi, and Rinko--to deliver unwelcome news about the next round of competition. Too bad they can't shoot him. Now it's a race against time as our friends hunt for hidden treasure in the Celestial World and battle wacky powers that are no joke--like the ability to turn puns into reality. Very punny-- not!
name: Vol. 11

description:
In Control

In an abandoned ghost town, Team Ueki faces off against Team Marilyn, which pulverizes all opponents in minutes. What's the secret to Marilyn's incredible success? Ueki's friends are about to find out the hard way, as Marilyn descends on Rinko at super speed and Ueki fights the knife expert Baron. But with a little extra training from Li Ho, Ueki makes a transformation that just might give him the edge!
name: Vol. 12

description:
Countdown!

Team Marilyn can't lose...as long as Marilyn's in charge! She's a powerhouse, mowing down every opponent she finds. Ueki's solution: hide! Now Marilyn is searching for Ueki, Ueki is searching for his teammates, and everyone's searching for the pendant that will win the battle. But with the clock running down, there's still time for Sano to learn a few new tricks--and for Mori to finally figure out what her power is!
name: Vol. 13

description:
Ambush!

The long-awaited moment has arrived: at last, Mori has finally figured out what her power is! Too bad it's not very useful in battle. Can Mori and her new power take on Memory, tactical genius and master of traps? If Ueki and his friends survive this round, they'll have to face Team Capucho--and a sneak attack from the ruthless Hanon!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 126: The Last Hand
  • Chapter 127: In the Med Room
  • Chapter 128: Unpredictable Development
  • Chapter 129: Which Do You Choose?
  • Chapter 130: Pagu
  • Chapter 131: Team Barrow
  • Chapter 132: Van, Rinko and the Sacred Weapon
  • Chapter 133: The Celestial Army
  • Chapter 134: A True Man
  • Chapter 135: Determination
name: Vol. 14

description:
Level Two!

Team Ueki has faced some tough teams in the third round...but a team made up entirely of Celestials? Mori and her irresistible spectacles are helpless against Kill Norton, who boasts a genius-level IQ and glasses of his own. And Sano is already injured going into his match with Barrow, whose power remains a mystery. But the worst is yet to come. How did Ueki suddenly drop down to zero stars?
name: Vol. 15

description:
Final Volume!

Ueki vs. Hanon!

Team Ueki knew the final battle wouldn't be easy, but what awaits them is beyond anything that's come before. Now wielding absolute power and following his own unhinged agenda, Hanon prepares to face Ueki atop a floating battlefield. Who will crown the next King of the Celestial World and win the Talent of Blank...and what will the winner do with this power?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 146: Hanon's Rules
  • Chapter 147: The Final Round Begins!
  • Chapter 148: Margaret's Plot
  • Chapter 149: Each and Every Emotion
  • Chapter 150: Don't Die
  • Chapter 151: Ueki vs. Hanon!
  • Chapter 152: The Image of Strength
  • Chapter 153: Final Battle!!
  • Final Chapter: The Talent of Blank
name: Vol. 16

description:
Collects issues 1-8, the Michael Turner issues, in one volume.

The story of how Sara Pezzini became the wielder of The Witchblade and her initial encounters with Kenneth Irons and Ian Nottingham.
name: TPB

description:
Welcome to...

Aria The Enchanted Collection

The Kingdom of Enchantment, a roadside theme park that flourished in the 1950s, has sat abandoned for decades. When a mysterious invitation literally drops into Kildare's lap, she is led to a remarkable discovery—a genuine magical kingdom hidden away in the Catskill Mountains. But a dark and terrible secret lies buried at the heart of this fairytale land, a reminder of the dangers of getting what you wish for.

The international award-winning story, finally brought to you in a stunning collection. Featuring the two part and hard to find ARIA: SUMMER SPELL and, as a TRUE BONUS, a never-seen-before Aria prose story written by Brian Holguin.
name: Vol. 3

description: Portions of this volume originally appeared under the title A DISTANT SOIL: IMMIGRANT SONG and A DISTANT SOIL: KNIGHTS OF THE ANGEL published by Donning Company in 1987/1989. Also revised and expanded, published in single-magazine issues A Distant Soil (vol 2) #1-13 Aria Press/Image.
name: The Gathering

person_credits.name: Colleen Doran
person_credits.role: writer, editor, penciler, letterer, cover, production

description: A small team of champions band together to protect young Liana from the Hierarchy, a corrupt otherworld government determined to destroy her. Unknown to the Hierarchy, Seren, their enshrined Avatar, a powerful psionic and religious leader, secretly aids Liana, and plots a coup to overthrow his masters.
name: The Ascendant

description:
Spider-Man's unmasking makes him the talk of the town and his pupils!

By Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa and Clayton Crain

Plus, he's just become every super villain's favourite target!

By Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa and Angel Medina

Classic Action: Peter Parker endures horrific trials, unaware that fate od the human race is in his hands!

By Tom DeFalco and and Tom Morgan.

Includes material reprinted from: Sensational Spider-Man #28-29, Amazing Spider-Man #274 and Spider-Man Unlimited #1

Collects Witchblade #9-19 AND The Darkness (vol 1) #9-10 an art gallery and the cover gallery.

New York City police detective Sara Pezzini is the reluctant bearer of the Witchblade, an ancient and mysterious mystical gauntlet that has bonded itself to her. Sara must resist the gauntlet's all-consuming thirst for battle, all the while solving the city's strangest crimes—many of which invariably seem to lead back to the WITCHBLADE!
name: Volume 2

description:
Discover the Origin of the Magalena! Armed with the Spear of Destiny, one of the thirteen Artifacts, The Magdalena is the Church's protector and monster hunter. The Order of the Magdalena has existed since the foundation of the Catholic Church and this stunning volume presents The Magdalena's first appearances in the Top Cow Universe.

This collected edition includes the first appearance of The Magdalena by Malachy Coney and superstar Joe Benitez from The Darkness vol 1 #15-18. Also collected is The Magdalena's first solo three-issue limited series Blood Divine by Marcia Chen and Joe Benitez. Additionally, this volume also showcases a cover gallery by superstar artists including Marc Silvestri, Michael Turner, and others!
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Star Trek: Countdown to Darkness (Compte à Rebours Avant les Ténèbres)

description: There are no holidays in August--at least until Alfred forces Batman to get out of Gotham for a few days. Bruce invites Selina to a tropical beach getaway, but with Catwoman sharing his yacht, buried treasure and pirates can't be too far behind
name: Tropical Getaway
